content: So good I bought the irl version.
Everybody should look into this and accept it's message. Is the corona virus a wake up call.
I am so happy with this app. I feel like my physical cards and virtual are interconnected now. Love my physical deck, but the mobility off the app is so handy.
Love these I use them and this app is ace

As a Bardic student of contemporary druidry, the imagery and explicative texts very adequately represent the 'feel' I seek and am inspired by. My wife has her own copy installed too and she also enjoys the nuances portrayed in these cards.
Amazingly versatile app, love it!

A lovely accompaniment to the card deck, but could also be used alone... either way the beautiful full color illustrations of each card are included. Having the full text card descriptions and meanings in my phone is super convenient, as is the option to journal and the "today's card" draw! Really a well designed and useful app. Update... one request/improvement as I've been using this for several months. A direct link from the card meaning (explore- select card- meaning) to the journal.
Fantastic! I have the original card deck also.
It's a great deck for me I love nature and spirit animals. These cards talk to me in a way I understand. This app is spectacular.

I just love the ease of using this app. I never have any problems with it. I also enjoy the clear and compelling artwork. There are also lots of layout options and the ability to share the results of a reading. Just love it!
Love this deck!

Love this deck, it's a real challenge to decipher but forces your mind to think outside the box. I also feel strangely connected to it, so if you are an earth element person it may resonate with you too.
I bought the app and deck in tandem and they work great. The app is easy to use and a great way to learn this fascinating, unorthodox deck. I love it!
Beautiful deck and layouts

I fell in love with this deck as soon as I opened the package. The deck I ordered didn't come with a book but I found this app and it has been a very valuable tool in helping me learn these unique cards. The app even has features that could allow you to do a reading without having a physical deck, although I strongly recommend you also purchase the deck. The app is easy to navigate and packed full of useful information and features.
A beautiful deck with nature scenes that invoke a wiccan/druidic feel.

I am giving this a 5 star rating because Fools Dog apps are all amazingly put together. However, the Wildwood Tarot is definitely not my favorite deck. Even for an experienced reader, it can be really difficult to read. Beautiful, though.
Wonderful set.Interpretation text is insightful and inspiring. The great art is full of unique symbolism that emphasises a mindful approach to being. Well worth the purchase.
Excellent

I got this app to learn about the wild wood tarot as I could'nt get the QR code on the box to work.I'm really glad I purchased it.It's a very helpful and informative app with everything you need to guide you through the wild wood tarot.I especially like card of the day which helps guide you through the day with positive thoughts and ideas.
was an amazing app well-made beautiful I have a physical deck as well and they never sent me a book so this works good for that is as well thank you so much
As good as the actual deck and book, but much more portable.
Really nice.
Fantastic, everything you could want in a tarot app
The pulls give so much insight. This app really feels like a phone based version of the deck.
Fantastic app for this wonderful deck. Very clear and easy to use.

Great tarot app n the cards are amazing I have both the deck n the app n they work great together. Will give 5 Stars if you guys add a feature that allows you to use the physical deck by picking a spread and choosing which cards fell in what position. Other than that this is a great app.

I got this deck for Christmas and it is beautiful! I downloaded the app immediately and it is well worth the money. Not only do you get a wonderfully interactive app that needs no physical deck, it contains the complete companion book for the Wild Wood Tarot. PLEASE create an app for the Sun and Moon Tarot! Still loving this app weeks later. I use it daily with and without my WWT deck. 2-26-2020 I still love this app a year later. I still use it daily.

I can't imagine what more I could want or need from this app. It even includes an e-reader version of the full book that comes with the physical deck! It is so easy to use that I sometimes will now use it for my morning reading instead of using the cards themselves, and the journaling feature helps me keep all of my reading notes in one place. It has several built in spreads to choose from, and also has an option to customize your own spreads. Top notch app. Truly impressed.
I have the the psyical Wildwood Tarot pack I'm very impressed with the app version.
Love this deck. All fool's tarot apps are great. My favorite is the freeform spread.
Awesome deck although graphics are not traditional but it have its own power.
Love this beautiful deck!
Well illustrated pagan, nature themed tarot deck harking back to more primitive times when people were more connected to natural cycles, animals and mythology.
Deep enduring and eco friendly deck.
Very accurate and convenient

Very well programmed and designed. With a lot of options. I can fully recommend this app!

I purchased the physical version of this deck last year and fell in love with it, and this app has helped me become more familiar with its imagery. I did the same with my first ever deck (Rider-Waite) and it was immensely helpful. Except this one has the option to place cards however I want in a reading, wonderful! wonderful artwork!

interpretations are unique to the deck which is kind of cool because it's not the usual king/queen/ace etc. and wand/cup/swords etc. interpretations. much more of an emphasis on nature. üëç

A great deck with beautiful illustrations and a perfectly laid out app to boot! The only thing I wish for is inverted card meanings. I manage well enough but it would make things a little easier. Perhaps just add an "INVERT" option when reading the card.

nice app. good readings too
I got this app as a companion for the physical deck, and it is worth penny. 10/10 would do again.
Beautiful, insightful and easy to use.

Absolutely marvellous. Ancient tradition, and shamanic wisdom passed down through the ages to bring the reader to that sacred place within where there is connectivity with All That Is from which guidance and having can be found.

Love this app! It allows me to have my favorite tarot guide books at all times without lugging them around. I get to test out new decks for ~$5 rather thand $25+ for book and decks. The journal feature allows me to keep track of readings so I can look back to review accuracy.
readings are very accurate. this app has been great for helping me learn new spreads
beautiful

This deck was a nice surprise.  I am used to seeing decks that are basically just variations on the standard Ryder-Waite artwork and interpretation.  This deck has a different slant in both respects.  Will Worthington's artwork is exquisite, with a strong nature-oriented, Ancient Celtic feel.  The drawings themselves and the interpretations have similarities to the standard, but are different enough that they bring something new to it.  You can access the full meanings from  Ryan and Mathews' book.  I like that they give you some options on the spreads, such as using major arcana only.  Another plus is that there ia a journal function, and the individual cards ask questions to help you think more deeply about the reading. This has quickly become one of my favorite tarot apps. Kudos to all involved in making it!
Great app!
